1. We just downloaded the code of an application. What is the base image used in the Dockerfile?
Inspect the Dockerfile in the webapp-color directory.
A:
You can either open the file using vi /root/webapp-color/Dockerfile (or using commands such as cat/more/less/vim e.t.c) and 
look for the FROM instruction or search for it directly using grep -i FROM /root/webapp-color/Dockerfile.

build an image:
docker build -t webapp-color .

run an instance of the image and publish port 8080 on the container to 8282 on the host:
docker run -p 8282:8080 webapp-color

